The paper discusses a novel algorithm for the recovery of compressive sampled signals under noisy conditions. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm, which could also fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses simulation studies to evaluate the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
